   vertebrates has not been reported. We examined the impact of Suwannee
   River humic acid (HA) on the toxicity of TiO(2)NPs to developing
   zebrafish (Danio rerio) in the dark and under simulated sunlight
   illumination. Adsorption of HA increased suspension stability and
   decreased TiO2NP exposure. TiO(2)NPs were more toxic in the presence of
   HA. In the absence of simulated sunlight, a small but significant
   increase in lethality was observed in fish exposed to TiO(2)NPs in the
   presence of HA. Under simulated sunlight illumination, photocatalytic
   degradation of HA reduced suspension stability. Despite the lower
   concentrations of Ti associated with fish in the treatments containing
   HA, under simulated sunlight illumination, median lethal concentrations
   were lower and oxidative DNA damage was elevated relative to fish
   exposed to TiO(2)NPs in the absence of HA. This study demonstrates the
   importance of considering environmental factors (i.e., exposure to
   sunlight, adsorption of DOM) when assessing the potential risks posed by
   engineered nanomaterials in the environment.
