   aliphatic/aromatic carbon and inner-sphere complexation with carboxyl
   functional groups, while SiO2 and ZnO mainly associated with HAs by weak
   interactions (e.g., van der Waals interactions). The present findings
   indicate that interactions between HA and metal-oxide colloids can
   substantially influence the desorption of U(VI) from these particles,
   thereby potentially affecting the mobility of this radionuclide in
   groundwater.
