   whereby stock dry powder nanoparticles are sonicated in pre-conditioned
   (with base, or acid, plus stabilizing agent) water, then diluted into
   culture media. The "condition and capture" principle is transferable to
   other nanoparticle and media chemistries: simultaneously, mechanically
   and electrostatically, nanoparticles can be dispersed with surrounding
