   correlation between DLVO energies or zeta-potential and flocculation
   parameters, as some OM has little effect on the DLVO interaction of
   montmorillonite colloids whereas other types of OM exert significant
   non-DLVO interactions such as repulsive hydration, steric repulsion, and
   polymer bridging. Further understanding of the physical-chemical
   properties of OM is needed in order to predict the flocculation
   behaviors of estuarine and coastal suspended colloids.
