   weight, type of carbon, and ligand density. Dynamic light scattering was
   employed to monitor the growth and aggregation of Zn-S-NOM nanoparticles
   in supersaturated solutions containing dissolved aquatic humic
   substances. The NOM was observed to reduce particle growth rates,
