   influence, and in some cases control, their surface properties and
   aggregation behavior. As a result, the understanding of nanoparticle
   fate, transport, and toxicity in natural systems must include a
   fundamental framework for predicting such behavior. Using a suite of
   gold nanoparticles (AuNPs) with different capping agents, the impact of
   surface functionality, presence of natural organic matter, and aqueous
   chemical composition (pH, ionic strength, and background electrolytes)
