   concentrations of divalent cations lead to enhanced aggregation. The
   colloidal stability of the NPs in the absence of NOM is a function of
   capping agent, pH, ionic strength, and electrolyte valence. In the
   presence of NOM at the conditions examined in this study, the capping
   agent is a less important determinant of stability, and the adsorption
   of NOM is a controlling factor.
